      • newClass

        private int newClass(boolean IsFromUML,
                     java.lang.String Filename,
                     int LineNumber,
                     java.lang.String ClassName,
                     java.lang.String AccessType,
                     boolean IsStatic,
                     boolean IsAbstract,
                     boolean IsFinal)
        Inserts a new record into either the UMLClass or CodeClass table. If IsFromUML = true the destination table will be UMLClass else the destination table will be CodeClass.
        Parameters:
        IsFromUML - Designates if the class is from a UML or Source Code document.
        Filename - Name of the file which the class originates.
        LineNumber - Line number within the originating file.
        ClassName - Name of the class.
        AccessType - Access identifier of the class (public, private, etc..)
        IsStatic - True if the class is static.
        IsAbstract - True if the class is abstract.
        IsFinal - True if the class is final.
        Returns:
        Auto-incremented Class_ID of the new record within the destination table.

      • Commit

        public void Commit()
        Commit must be called to save data changes made by NewUML, NewSource, Match, and Relate methods.

      • IsInitialized

        public boolean IsInitialized()
        Returns:
        true if the database has been initialized.

      • IsOpen

        public boolean IsOpen()
        Returns:
        true if a database connection has been opened.

      • Relate

        public void Relate()
        Relates Class_ID of Attribute, Method, and Reference entries.

      • Match

        public void Match()
        Updates Other_ID of each table record to the corresponding ID of the opposite type. Calculates NumMismatched value of each record.

      • ReInitDatabase

        public void ReInitDatabase()
        Re-initializes the database. Calls Close() sets _isInit and _hasCreatedDB to false then calls Open() and InitDatabase(). This deletes the database and re-creates it using new structures.

      • InitDatabase

        public void InitDatabase()
        Creates the database structures.

      • Open

        public boolean Open()
        Opens a connection to the database.
        Returns:
        true if the database is open. false if there was an error.

      • Close

        public boolean Close()
        Closes a connection to the database.
        Returns:
        true if the database is closed. false if an error occurred.
